column5: Ya all know my pick        No I dont share me toys.LOL
got my vote as well, hoping for a great year.   jason
What fishing tourney is that one on. Can't seem to see a spot for a casting platform or electric motor so must be for downrigging!!!
It,s about to begin and I got the treats made just in time.  Turkey kabasa , herb shrimp, veggie crackers,grapes and some chillie wings.  GO 88.
Cough, cough....................... I feel another Thursday afternoon cold coming on.

Geez, do you think enough drives changed numbers and colours this year.  Hard to figure out who is driving what at first.  Tony is now 14 and drives for Stewart-Haas Racing, red and white, Old Spice and Office Depot.  At least I look better in red than orange
BTW, Nice DOLL Brian, not that there's anything wrong with that
Last time I saw it it was riding on his shoulder in the truck Joey !
Yes you will and I might even leave your tickets at the door.  Jr.. screwed that one up !

How do you figure that one??????????????? What did he do wrong????  Junior showed the power..Five laps to the front,then it was a restart, and Jr to the front again. Pitstop,mix it up,stuck in the middle.poop happens. Sunday is qualifiying. Any takers on the pole sitter? or maybe the winner?  They all know that JR is the one to beat,so they will gang up on him. Guys like Tony the smoke,(god bless Tony Joey)will help him out til the end.Then it all for themselves.
I'll take Bill Elliot for the pole. Seriously.
I wont take that bet ,as I feal the same. I love the jr man,but man is Bill fast or what?. Woods is making a come back.
Nice to see Bill up there in the top ten for next sunday Dan.  Truex,what a surprise,or maybe it,s not. DEI. Jr is right where he needs to be.

Gotta love the Bud shoot out I like the new format it sure was a great race I know I will be heading out for work early Thursday to make it home for 2 now if I cna just get my daughter to walk home from school it could save ten laps.  The only real bad part of the shootout is that the 18 did not land on his roof well I can only hope for next Sunday.   As for a winner I would love to see Martin win his first 500 but would not be sad to have Happy take it away again.
